{"id":"239667955_3-Coloring_in_Time_O13289n","abstract":"We consider worst case time bounds for NP-complete problems including 3-SAT,\n3-coloring, 3-edge-coloring, and 3-list-coloring. Our algorithms are based on a\nconstraint satisfaction (CSP) formulation of these problems. 3-SAT is\nequivalent to (2,3)-CSP while the other problems above are special cases of\n(3,2)-CSP; there is also a natural duality transformation from (a,b)-CSP to\n(b,a)-CSP. We give a fast algorithm for (3,2)-CSP and use it to improve the\ntime bounds for solving the other problems listed above. Our techniques involve\na mixture of Davis-Putnam-style backtracking with more sophisticated matching\nand network flow based ideas.","authors":["Richard Beigel","David Eppstein"],"meta":["February 2005Journal of Algorithms 54(2):168-204","DOI:10.1016/j.jalgor.2004.06.008","SourcearXiv"],"references":["222871662_Solving_satisfiability_in_less_than_2n_steps","3785061_An_Improved_Exponential-Time_Algorithm_for_k-SAT","2825720_A_Spectral_Technique_for_Coloring_Random_3-Colorable_Graphs","2753508_An_Exact_Parallel_Algorithm_For_The_Maximum_Clique_Problem","2513379_Algorithms_for_Constraint_Satisfaction_Problems_A_Survey","304822955_Small_maximal_independent_sets_and_faster_exact_graph_coloring","279540844_O20_3_0_4_N_ALGORITHM_FOR_SOLVING_MAXIMUM_INDEPENDENT_SET_PROBLEM","268852186_Obere_Komplexitatsschranken_fur_TAUT-Entscheidungen","266216568_Chromatic_Number_in_Time_O24023_n_Using_Maximal_Independent_Sets","262244045_An_O_n_314_-coloring_algorithm_for_3-colorable_graphs","256181513_A_note_on_the_complexity_of_the_chromatic_number_problem","250663928_Two_systems_for_proving_tautologies_based_on_the_split_method","248307703_Various_upper_bounds_on_the_complexity_of_algorithms_for_deciding_propositional_tautolo-gies","245583703_Better_worst-case_upper_bounds_for_MAX2SAT","244954154_A_Computing_Procedure_for_Quantification_Theory","238392597_Solving_3_-_satisfiability_in_less_than_1","229646573_A_Simple_Alg